<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-28T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-28T05:00:00-05:00" n="285" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 294/41: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Observer on the Rhineland High
                                    Commission</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Allen</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Coblenz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-28T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 28,
                                            1920—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:45
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>German custodian of Government property agrees to pay expenses
                                connected American representation High Commission and also past
                                expenses to date. Request disposition of latter funds when received.
                                Reference my former telegram,<note n="42" xml:id="d285fn42">Not
                                    printed.</note> State Department funds no longer necessary for
                                operation this office.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Allen</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>